        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figures 1–18. Adult specimens of Neolucia hobartensis: (1–3) N. hobartensis hobartensis lectotype male (QM) showing upperside, underside and labels; (4–7) N. hobartensis hobartensis from Tasmania: 4 and 5, male upperside and underside “Pine Tier Lake, TAS, S42.04.14, E146.28.74, 16th Jan. 2013, G.E. Wurtz” (GEWC), 6 and 7, female upperside and underside “Mt. Barrow, T. 4000 ft., 4 Mar. 1963, I.F.B. Common & M.S. Upton” (ANIC); (8–11) N. hobartensis albolineata ssp. nov. from ACT and southern NSW: 8 and 9, holotype male upperside and underside “Smokers Gap, ACT, 25 DEC. 1998, M.F. Braby” (ANIC), 10 and 11, paratype female upperside and underside “E.D. EDWARDS, 25.1.70, Boyd R, N.S.W., AUSTRALIA” (ANIC); (12–15) N. hobartensis monticola from northern NSW: 12 and 13, male upperside and underside “Barrington Tops, NSW, 23 Jan. 1987, J.F.R. Kerr” (ANIC), 14 and 15, female upperside and underside “Barrington Tops, NSW, 23 Jan. 1987, J.F.R. Kerr” (ANIC); (16–18) N. hobartensis monticola lectotype male (AMS) showing upperside, underside and labels." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4677146/files/figure.png" .

